==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exigency
<hw>Ex"i*gen*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Exigencies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[LL.
<ets>exigentia</ets>: cf. F. <ets>exigence</ets>.]</ety> <def>The state
of being exigent; urgent or exacting want; pressing necessity or
distress; need; a case demanding immediate action, supply, or remedy;
<as>as, an unforeseen <ex>exigency</ex></as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The present
<xex>exigency</xex> of his affairs.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Ludlow.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Demand; urgency; distress; pressure; emergency;
necessity; crisis.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exigendary</ent>⟦br⟧
